===Etymology===
The origin and meaning of the name “Amuzgo” is unclear, and there are several theories. It seems likely that the name comes from one of the many [[Nahuatl]] languages ([[w:Uto-Aztecan languages|Uto-Aztecan]] language family): (1) One claim says that it comes from Nahuatl '''amoxco''' and means ''‘Place of Books’''; (2) another is that it began as '''amuchco''' (''‘where there is tin’''), composed of '''amuchitl''' ([[tin]]) and '''-co''' (in, at); (3) a third idea is that it comes from Nahuatl '''amochitl''' and means ''‘where there is [[copper]]’''.

===Noun===
'''Amuzgo'''

# An indigenous language of Mexico ([[w:Oto-Manguean languages|Oto-Manguean language family]]) with about 30,000 speakers, mostly in Oaxaca state.

